    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180\u00b0C/ 160\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Deseed your<strong> peppers</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min until roasted and golden \u2013 these are your <strong>roasted peppers</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable\u00a0stock mix </strong>in 700ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, then add your<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and <strong>red chilli relish </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> sweet tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based\u00a0pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced\u00a0onion</strong>\u00a0with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4 min until softened but not browned</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>arborio\u00a0rice</strong>, <strong>chopped\u00a0garlic</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>ground\u00a0turmeric</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min further</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 1/3 of the <strong>sweet tomato stock</strong> and stir continuously until absorbed</p><p>Continue to add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>sweet tomato stock</strong>, a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min, until all the stock has absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>risotto</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> from the oven</p><p>Stir <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>roasted pepper</strong> into the risotto (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Remove the<strong> </strong>risotto from the heat and stir in<strong> half</strong> of the <strong>grated cheese </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped chives </strong>(save the rest for garnish!), then season with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>sweet mixed pepper & chive risotto</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-mixed-pepper-and-chive-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, top the<strong> sweet mixed pepper & chive risotto</strong> with the <strong>reserved roasted pepper</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated cheese </strong>and the <strong>pine kernel & seed mix</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> reserved chopped chives</strong> and a<strong> </strong>drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
